      "body" : "Hmm I think I get the URL part; it's not about the HTTP protocol itself, but the endpoint is encoded in the form `http://user:pass@127.0.0.1/`.\r\nIn this case you need to url-encode the password. So this doesn't work:\r\n\r\n    http://user:/PASS/@127.0.0.1/`\r\n\r\nBut this should:\r\n\r\n    http://user:%2FPASS%2F@127.0.0.1/`\r\n\r\nIt can be dangerous to skip this quoting step (use `urllib.quote('/PASS/','')`).\r\n",
